@startuml Actor Position Battle Return Sequence

skinparam shadowing false
hide footbox

title Actor Position - Encounter Snapshot and Battle Return

participant ExplorationMode
participant EventCenter
participant EncounterEmitter
participant EncounterService
participant BattleService
participant BattleContext
participant ModeManager
participant BattleMode
participant ActorManager
participant ActorPathDriver
participant ActorData
participant "ActorData.Position" as Position
participant ActorPresenter
participant WorldPathfinder
participant VoxelTraversalUtility
participant WorldPresenter

== Encounter Captures Return Cell ==

ExplorationMode -> EventCenter : EmitPlayerMoved(targetCell)
EventCenter -> EncounterEmitter : PlayerMoved(targetCell)
EncounterEmitter -> WorldPathfinder : TryResolveStandingCell(targetCell approximate point)
WorldPathfinder --> EncounterEmitter : standingCell

EncounterEmitter -> EncounterService : RequestBattle(boardConfiguration, standingCell, standingCell, team, placementStyle, true)
EncounterService -> EventCenter : EmitBattleLaunchRequested(..., playerReturnWorldCell = standingCell, ...)
EventCenter -> BattleService : BattleLaunchRequested(...)
BattleService -> BattleContext : new BattleContext(..., returnWorldCell = standingCell)
BattleService -> EventCenter : EmitBattleStarted(battleContext)

EventCenter -> ModeManager : BattleStarted(battleContext)
ModeManager -> BattleMode : Enter(battleContext)

note right of BattleContext
  ReturnWorldCell is only a transition snapshot.
  It is not the live actor position source.
  Live position remains ActorData.Position.
end note

== Battle Ends ==

BattleService -> EventCenter : EmitBattleResolved(battleContext, winner)
EventCenter -> ModeManager : BattleResolved(battleContext, winner)

ModeManager -> BattleMode : Exit()
ModeManager -> ExplorationMode : Enter(gameContext, battleContext.ReturnWorldCell)

== Re-enter Exploration at Return Cell ==

ExplorationMode -> ActorManager : TrySetWorldCell(actor, returnWorldCell)

alt actor has a movement driver
    ActorManager -> ActorPathDriver : Stop()
end

ActorManager -> WorldPathfinder : TryResolveStandingCell(approximate return cell point)
WorldPathfinder --> ActorManager : resolvedReturnCell
ActorManager -> VoxelTraversalUtility : TryGetStandingWorldPoint(resolvedReturnCell)
VoxelTraversalUtility --> ActorManager : returnWorldPosition

ActorManager -> ActorData : SetPosition(returnWorldPosition, forceNotify = true)
ActorData -> Position : Set(returnWorldPosition, true)
Position -> ActorPresenter : Changed(returnWorldPosition)
ActorPresenter -> ActorPresenter : transform.position = returnWorldPosition

ExplorationMode -> ActorManager : TryGetWorldCell(actor)
ActorManager -> ActorData : read Position.Value
ActorManager -> WorldPathfinder : TryResolveStandingCell(Position.Value)
WorldPathfinder --> ActorManager : actorWorldCell

ExplorationMode -> WorldPresenter : LoadImmediatelyAroundWorldCell(actorWorldCell)
ExplorationMode -> EventCenter : EmitPlayerChunkChanged(currentChunk)
EventCenter -> WorldPresenter : PlayerChunkChanged(currentChunk)
WorldPresenter -> WorldPresenter : ApplyLoadResult(Load(currentChunk))

note over ExplorationMode, EncounterEmitter
  ExplorationMode does not emit PlayerMoved during Enter.
  Returning to an encounter cell therefore does not immediately start the same fight again.
end note

@enduml
